{"POA":[{"def":"A genus of grasses, including a great number of species, as the kinds called meadow grass, Kentucky blue grass, June grass, and spear grass (which see).","pos":""}],"POACH":[{"def":"To cook, as eggs, by breaking them into boiling water; also, to cook with butter after breaking in a vessel.","pos":""},{"def":"To rob of game; to pocket and convey away by stealth, as game; hence, to plunder.","pos":""}],"POACHER":[{"def":"The American widgeon.","pos":""}],"POACHINESS":[{"def":"The state of being poachy; marshiness.","pos":""}],"POACHY":[{"def":"Wet and soft; easily penetrated by the feet of cattle; -- said of land POAK; POAKE Poak, Poake, n.","pos":""},{"def":"Waste matter from the preparation of skins, consisting of hair, lime, oil, etc.","pos":""}]}